text:
Hi Katie!

I'm very sorry for such a late reply, I've seen this message a while ago but couldn't find time to properly go through it and reply, the uni workload is pretty intense.:(

Thanks so so much for all of this information, it's super useful! We've decided for sure that this year we won't do the full muscle system because of the time but I'd definitely want to delve into learning siming when I find time, so all this stuff will become very handy.

Thanks for looking at the script! We've changed our idea now though as we had a lot of struggle coming up with magic tricks that would include manageable FX and animation as we want to make it as realistic as possible. So, now we came up with chef monkey idea!:D It's basically a series of dreamy glamorous ratatouille-esque shots set at night of the white-faced capuchin cooking, mixing soup, chopping herbs in a beautifully lit kitchen, set to lovely French jazzy music; the monkey is being a real artisan about it - until the end when the owner of the house comes in wearing a dressing gown and timidly wielding a baseball bat, flicks on the lights to reveal an absolutely wrecked mess of a kitchen with pots and ingredients everywhere, smoke pooling out of the oven and our monkey sitting in the middle of it. I'll put the rough storyboard that we have, so maybe it'll be easier to visualise.:))
I've retopologised and UV'ed the monkey already, so groom and rigging artists now can for more efficiently .
sorry for the spam with retopologised version!:D
I just noticed that storyboard that I've uploaded before is pretty low res, so impossible to read. Sending again!
